OVER THE REMAINING LIFE OF THE RESPECTIVE DEBT INSTRUMENTS USING THE

EFFECTIVE-INTEREST METHOD. THE AMORTIZATION OF THE FAIR VALUE ADJUSTMENT

REDUCED INTEREST EXPENSE BY $54 MILLION AND $55 MILLION FOR THE YEARS ENDED

DECEMBER 31, 2005 AND 2004, RESPECTIVELY.

