FARINA V.

TRAVELERS PROPERTY CASUALTY CORP., ET AL.

(JUD. DIST. OF WATERBURY,

CT. DECEMBER 15, 2003).  THE

FARINA

COMPLAINT ALSO NAMED SPC AND ITS FORMER SUBSIDIARY, ADAMS

ACQUISITION CORP., AS DEFENDANTS, ALLEGING THAT THEY AIDED AND ABETTED THE

ALLEGED BREACH OF FIDUCIARY DUTY.  ON MARCH 18, 2004, TPC AND SPC

ANNOUNCED THAT ALL OF THESE LAWSUITS HAD BEEN SETTLED, SUBJECT TO COURT

APPROVAL. BEFORE COURT APPROVAL OF THE SETTLEMENT, ADDITIONAL SHAREHOLDER

LITIGATION WAS COMMENCED, AS DESCRIBED BELOW. ON SEPTEMBER 12, 2005,

PLAINTIFFS VOLUNTARILY WITHDREW THEIR COMPLAINTS WITHOUT PREJUDICE.

